column1: Table 7: Age and sex structure of administrative areas, mid-2018

1) 2018 Council areas and 2018 NHS Board areas. The 2018 areas differ from the previous 2011 Council areas and 2014 NHS Board areas due to a small boundary change at Keltybridge (which did not affect the population), between Fife and Tayside.
2) Working age at 30 June 2018 is defined as men aged 16 to 64 and women aged 16 to approximately 64 years and 268 days.
3) Pensionable age at 30 June 2018 was 65 for men and approximately 64 years and 269 days for women.
4) The sex ratio is the male population divided by the female population.
